The 'Stockholm metro' () is a metro system in Stockholm, Sweden. The first line
opened in 1950, and today the system has 100 stations in use, of which 47 are
underground and 53 above ground. There are seven lines numbered from 10 to 19,
in three groups identified by a color: the Green, Red and Blue lines. Each color
line has two or three numbered lines on shared sections through the Stockholm
City Centre.

The long metro system is owned by the Stockholm County Council through
Storstockholms Lokaltrafik (SL). The operation is contracted to MTR
Corporation ().
